observations.recommendation:
2.8	We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the HRMO:
a.	Come up with a concrete policy guideline relative to the hiring and rehiring of JO personnel to establish a clear expectation and protect the rights of both the employees and the Municipality;
b.	Provide Statement of Duties and Responsibilities of JO personnel to clearly identify their responsibilities and perform their duties efficiently;
c.	Set a standard wage rate based on their qualifications and suitability for the job applied, subject to the Municipality’s financial capacity; and
d.	Install a biometrics system for JO personnel to properly monitor their DTRs;
2.9	We further recommended that the Municipal Mayor or their authorized representative provide a written justification for the 53 Job Orders that were absent during the headcount, along with a valid document and identification proving their existence.

We reiterate our previous recommendation that Management require the:
a) Municipal General Services Officer to submit a Report of the Physical Inventory of Property, Plant and Equipment for the year 2018 and to maintain updated Property Cards as prescribed by Section 119 & 124 of COA Circular No. 2002-003;
b) Municipal Accountant to maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards, Real Property Ledger Cards as prescribed by COA Circular No. 2002-003.
